00:16:07,006 --> 00:16:09,473
It's really juicy,
the meat's just fall‐apart.

494
00:16:09,473 --> 00:16:11,373
I'm hungry.
So, what are we making?

495
00:16:11,373 --> 00:16:13,873
Beer‐butter injection
for the brisket.
Fire away.

496
00:16:13,873 --> 00:16:16,740
We hit it with the butter,
onions, minced garlic,

497
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:19,306
beef broth, brown sugar,
chili powder.

498
00:16:19,306 --> 00:16:20,573
Okay.
Dark beer.

499
00:16:20,573 --> 00:16:22,440
I've been thirsty
the whole time.

500
00:16:24,206 --> 00:16:26,740
Oh, it's ‐‐
‐Oh, yeah, it's for the...

501
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:27,906
How long is this
gonna cook down?

502
00:16:27,906 --> 00:16:29,173
About 10‐15 minutes.

503
00:16:29,173 --> 00:16:31,273
‐Puree it?
‐Yep.

504
00:16:31,273 --> 00:16:32,806
Sauce is done.
Dry rub?

505
00:16:32,806 --> 00:16:36,473
Yep. Smoked paprika,
brown sugar, celery salt,

506
00:16:36,473 --> 00:16:39,173
sea salt, pepper,
and allspice.

507
00:16:39,173 --> 00:16:41,040
[ Whistles ]
A lot of allspice.
Yeah, man.

508
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,273
That's the Norwegian.

509
00:16:42,273 --> 00:16:44,606
And here's our brisket.
Ready to go.

510
00:16:44,606 --> 00:16:46,773
Inject it with
the SpitJack Injector.
Yeah.

511
00:16:46,773 --> 00:16:48,506
Normally, we try to do
about eight vials.

512
00:16:48,506 --> 00:16:50,706
On one brisket?
On one, big brisket.

513
00:16:50,706 --> 00:16:52,640
Yeah, dude.

514
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:54,406
Okay,
so dry‐rub it.

515
00:16:54,406 --> 00:16:56,273
How long's
this gonna go down?

516
00:16:56,273 --> 00:16:57,273
12‐14 hours.

517
00:16:57,273 --> 00:16:58,573
‐225?
‐Yep.

518
00:16:58,573 --> 00:17:00,280
Next up.
