524
00:17:07,913 --> 00:17:09,246
apple cider vinegar.

525
00:17:09,246 --> 00:17:11,280
A little shot of water
just to thin her out.

526
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,680
Let this cook down
how long?

527
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,880
About 10 minutes.

528
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,280
You go right from there
to a squirt bottle,

529
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,346
and we're good to go?
Yep.

530
00:17:16,346 --> 00:17:17,613
‐I like it, buddy.
‐Okay.

531
00:17:17,613 --> 00:17:18,980
‐Pull the brisket?
‐Yeah.

532
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:21,746
And we let these briskets rest
for about 2 to 3 hours.

533
00:17:21,746 --> 00:17:24,046
Nice,
little smoke ring there.

534
00:17:24,046 --> 00:17:28,413
We got a pub roll
from a local bakery.

535
00:17:28,413 --> 00:17:29,513
Mmm.

536
00:17:29,513 --> 00:17:30,846
I pick that allspice up
right off the bat.

537
00:17:30,846 --> 00:17:31,880
Yeah.

538
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,113
Pick up a little bit
of that beer.

539
00:17:34,113 --> 00:17:35,880
Not dry by any means.

540
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:39,046
♪♪♪♪

541
00:17:39,046 --> 00:17:40,546
That's pretty dynamite.

542
00:17:40,546 --> 00:17:42,380
No offense to your bun here,
I'm just...

543
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:45,346
[ Laughs ]
None taken, man.

544
00:17:45,346 --> 00:17:47,446
That is the lingonberry
barbecue sauce.

545
00:17:47,446 --> 00:17:49,580
Lingonberry.
That is definitely Norweigian.

546
00:17:49,580 --> 00:17:51,146
Yep.

547
00:17:51,146 --> 00:17:53,646
Oh, that's lingonberry
and allspice all day long.

548
00:17:53,646 --> 00:17:56,846
That's good sauce.

549
00:17:56,846 --> 00:17:58,046
None on my face, right?

550
00:17:58,046 --> 00:17:59,786
‐No, you're good.
‐I'm good.

551
00:17:59,786 --> 00:18:01,420
Okay,
we've got a brisket combo.

552
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:04,186
Just so tender. It just melts
